description:
Repost : @let_them_feel_our_movement_ 

This is so true no lives matters in a world that strips us from our purpose meaning and eternal destination that only exists in the eyes of our biblical creator.  In a secular world view we are reduced to expendable merchandise to be bought sold and destroyed at leisure attributing value to ourselves from empty vanity which is only a distraction from the fact that we are truly empty with out being  redeemed and purposeful to the eternal will of the creator.  When we have to self declare that our lives matters to others who have shown that it doesn't we are just deluding ourselves with a lie that cuts us off from the source of all meaning and truth from God. The only life that matters is the one delivered from death and purified from sin to live eternally.
